# Work

You are working inside a task worktree for **{{.Branch}}**. Work is a multi-task orchestrator that decomposes plans into tasks with dependencies, then runs each task as a separate Claude Code instance in its own git worktree.

Use the `/work-plan` slash command to start the planning workflow.

## Workspace

Your workspace is at `workspace/`. Use it for all planning documents.

## Available Commands

```bash
work ls                 # List subtasks with their status
work show <id>          # Show details of a subtask
work tree               # Show subtask dependency tree
work tree <id>          # Show subtree rooted at a subtask
work ready              # Show subtasks ready to work on (no pending dependencies)
work active             # Show subtasks currently being worked on
work complete <id>      # Mark a subtask as complete
work rm <id>            # Remove a subtask
```

## Key Files

- `workspace/plan.md` — The implementation plan (created during `/work-plan`)
- `workspace/tasks/` — Subtask JSON files (created via the work MCP tool)
